distracted by running thoughts about mundane tasks? distracted by the cacophony of construction work down the street? distracted by the tag on your blouse rubbing your neck? "i notice myself thinking. hearing. feeling. i choose to refocus on my breath."

especially for those of us with ADHD, PTSD, ASD, etc. a "clear mind" "free of thoughts or distractions" is a totally unreasonable standard to hold ourselves to and imo defeats the purpose of the exercise. now you're layering judgements onto your thoughts instead of letting go.
my personal mantra: my body is a mountain. my mind is the sky. my thoughts are clouds that go drifting by.

if you got scammed into believing  mindfulness/meditation are about having a completely clear mind free of any thoughts or distractions, i have news for you. you haven't failed. just acknowledge the act of thinking/hearing/feeling/etc and return your attention to your breathing.
